HEADWORD: Abhominable
<hw>Ab*hom"i*na*ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Abominable.</def> <note>[A false orthography anciently used;
<xex>h</xex> was foisted into various words; hence <xex>abholish</xex>,
for <xex>abolish</xex>, etc.]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is <qex>abhominable</qex>, which he [Don Armado] would call
<qex>abominable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak. Love's Labor's Lost, v.
1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abhominal</ent>⟦br⟧
